+# Bob Foreman Architecture
+
+**IBM Bob Coding Challenge 2026**
+
+Bob Foreman orchestriert parallele Bob CLI Instanzen mit git worktree Isolation. Jeder Worker lâ”śĂ±uft in eigenem worktree, isoliert von anderen Tasks.
+
+## System Overview
+
+```mermaid
+graph TB
+    User[User] -->|triggers| FB[foreman-build.ps1]
+    FB -->|1. estimate| BE[Bob CLI - Plan Mode]
+    FB -->|2. spawn N jobs| SW1[spawn-worker.ps1 #1]
+    FB -->|2. spawn N jobs| SW2[spawn-worker.ps1 #2]
+    FB -->|2. spawn N jobs| SWN[spawn-worker.ps1 #N]
+    
+    SW1 -->|creates| WT1[worktrees/1/]
+    SW2 -->|creates| WT2[worktrees/2/]
+    SWN -->|creates| WTN[worktrees/N/]
+    
+    WT1 -->|runs| BC1[Bob CLI]
+    WT2 -->|runs| BC2[Bob CLI]
+    WTN -->|runs| BCN[Bob CLI]
+    
+    BC1 -->|writes| L1[logs/1.json]
+    BC2 -->|writes| L2[logs/2.json]
+    BCN -->|writes| LN[logs/N.json]
+    
+    FB -->|writes| FS[.foreman/state]
+    SW1 -->|updates| FS
+    SW2 -->|updates| FS
+    SWN -->|updates| FS
+    
+    FS -->|reads| SS[status-server.cjs :3001]
+    SS -->|serves| API[/dashboard/status.json]
+    API -->|polls| DH[dashboard/index.html]
+    DH -->|displays| Browser[User Browser]
+    
+    API -->|polls| TB[Telegram MCP Bot]
+    TB -->|posts| Phone[User Phone]
+    
+    style FB fill:#e1f5ff
+    style SS fill:#fff4e1
+    style DH fill:#e8f5e9
+    style TB fill:#f3e5f5
+```
+
+## Core Components
+
+### 1. foreman-build.ps1
+
+Top-level Orchestrator. Koordiniert gesamten Build-Prozess.
+
+**Ablauf:**
+1. Reset state (`.foreman/` cleanup)
+2. Bob estimate via plan-mode
+3. Mark `start_time.txt`
+4. Spawn N workers als PowerShell Background Jobs
+5. `Wait-Job` auf alle Workers
+6. Mark `end_time.txt`
+
+**State Files:**
+- `.foreman/estimate.json` - Bob's Schâ”śĂ±tzung (coins, time)
+- `.foreman/start_time.txt` - ISO timestamp
+- `.foreman/end_time.txt` - ISO timestamp
+
+**Code Pattern:**
+```powershell
+# Reset
+Remove-Item .foreman/tasks/*.json -Force
+
+# Estimate
+bob --mode plan @.foreman-prompts/task.txt | Out-File .foreman/estimate.json
+
+# Mark start
+Get-Date -Format o | Out-File .foreman/start_time.txt
+
+# Spawn workers
+$jobs = 1..4 | ForEach-Object {
+    Start-Job -FilePath .\scripts\spawn-worker.ps1 -ArgumentList $_
+}
+
+# Wait
+$jobs | Wait-Job
+
+# Mark end
+Get-Date -Format o | Out-File .foreman/end_time.txt
+```
+
+### 2. spawn-worker.ps1
+
+Worker Process. Einer pro Task, lâ”śĂ±uft als Background Job.
+
+**Ablauf:**
+1. `git worktree add -B worker/<id> worktrees/<id> master` (race-safe)
+2. Write `.foreman/tasks/<id>.json` Ă”ĂĄĂ† `status: "queued"`
+3. Update status Ă”ĂĄĂ† `"running"`
+4. `Set-Location worktrees/<id>`
+5. Execute `bob @prompt.txt`
+6. Capture output Ă”ĂĄĂ† `logs/<id>.json`
+7. Commit changes in worktree
+8. Update status Ă”ĂĄĂ† `"done"`
+
+**State Tracking:**
+```json
+{
+  "id": 1,
+  "status": "running",
+  "prompt": "task-1.txt",
+  "started_at": "2026-05-02T10:30:00Z",
+  "completed_at": null
+}
+```
+
+**Race Safety:**
+Git worktree add mit `-B` flag ist atomic. Parallele Calls kollidieren nicht.
+
+**Code Pattern:**
+```powershell
+param($WorkerId)
+
+# Create worktree
+git worktree add -B "worker/$WorkerId" "worktrees/$WorkerId" master
+
+# Update status
+@{ id=$WorkerId; status="running" } | ConvertTo-Json | Out-File ".foreman/tasks/$WorkerId.json"
+
+# Run Bob
+Set-Location "worktrees/$WorkerId"
+bob @../.foreman-prompts/task-$WorkerId.txt | Tee-Object -FilePath "../../logs/$WorkerId.json"
+
+# Commit
+git add -A
+git commit -m "Worker $WorkerId completed"
+
+# Mark done
+@{ id=$WorkerId; status="done" } | ConvertTo-Json | Out-File "../../.foreman/tasks/$WorkerId.json"
+```
+
+### 3. status-server.cjs
+
+Express Server auf Port 3001. Aggregiert State fâ”śâ•ťr Dashboard.
+
+**Endpoint:**
+- `GET /dashboard/status.json`
+
+**Data Sources:**
+- `.foreman/tasks/*.json` - Worker status
+- `.foreman/start_time.txt` - Build start
+- `.foreman/end_time.txt` - Build end
+- `.foreman/estimate.json` - Bob's estimate
+- `logs/*.setup.log` - Worker discovery
+- `logs/<id>.json` - Coin counts
+
+**Response Schema:**
+```json
+{
+  "estimated": { "coins": 1500, "time_seconds": 120 },
+  "elapsed_seconds": 45,
+  "saved_seconds": 75,
+  "is_complete": false,
+  "workers": [
+    {
+      "id": 1,
+      "status": "done",
+      "coins": 350,
+      "started_at": "2026-05-02T10:30:00Z",
+      "completed_at": "2026-05-02T10:31:15Z"
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+**CORS:**
+Enabled fâ”śâ•ťr Browser-Zugriff.
+
+**Code Pattern:**
+```javascript
+app.get('/dashboard/status.json', (req, res) => {
+  const tasks = fs.readdirSync('.foreman/tasks')
+    .map(f => JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(`.foreman/tasks/${f}`)));
+  
+  const estimate = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('.foreman/estimate.json'));
+  const startTime = new Date(fs.readFileSync('.foreman/start_time.txt', 'utf8'));
+  const elapsed = (Date.now() - startTime) / 1000;
+  
+  res.json({
+    estimated: estimate,
+    elapsed_seconds: elapsed,
+    saved_seconds: estimate.time_seconds - elapsed,
+    workers: tasks
+  });
+});
+```
+
+### 4. dashboard/index.html
+
+Vanilla HTML/JS Dashboard. Kein Framework.
+
+**Features:**
+- Polling `/dashboard/status.json` (1s interval)
+- 3 Metric Cards:
+  - **Estimated** - Bob's pre-flight Schâ”śĂ±tzung
+  - **Elapsed** - Live timer (100ms update)
+  - **Saved** - Estimated minus Elapsed (grâ”śâ•ťn wenn positiv, golden wenn done)
+- Worker Cards:
+  - Color-coded borders (queued=gray, running=blue, done=green, error=red)
+  - Status badges
+  - Coin counter per worker
+
+**UI Logic:**
+```javascript
+setInterval(async () => {
+  const data = await fetch('http://localhost:3001/dashboard/status.json').then(r => r.json());
+  
+  // Update elapsed (live)
+  const elapsed = data.elapsed_seconds;
+  document.getElementById('elapsed').textContent = formatTime(elapsed);
+  
+  // Update saved (color logic)
+  const saved = data.saved_seconds;
+  const savedEl = document.getElementById('saved');
+  savedEl.textContent = formatTime(Math.abs(saved));
+  savedEl.className = saved > 0 ? 'positive' : 'negative';
+  if (data.is_complete && saved > 0) savedEl.className = 'golden';
+  
+  // Update workers
+  data.workers.forEach(w => {
+    const card = document.getElementById(`worker-${w.id}`);
+    card.className = `worker-card ${w.status}`;
+    card.querySelector('.coins').textContent = w.coins;
+  });
+}, 1000);
+```
+
+### 5. Telegram MCP Bot
+
+MCP Server postet Status alle 10 Minuten auf Handy.
+
+**Trigger:**
+Cron-like interval (10min).
+
+**Message Format:**
+```
+Â­Ć’Ă±Ă» Bob Foreman Status
+Ă”Ă…â–’Â´Â©Ă… Elapsed: 2m 15s
+Â­Ć’Ă†â–‘ Saved: +45s
+Ă”ÂŁĂ  Workers: 3/4 done
+```
+
+**Integration:**
+Konsumiert `/dashboard/status.json` via HTTP.
+
+## Execution Flow
+
+```mermaid
+sequenceDiagram
+    participant User
+    participant FB as foreman-build.ps1
+    participant Bob as Bob CLI (Plan)
+    participant Job1 as Background Job 1
+    participant Job2 as Background Job 2
+    participant SW1 as spawn-worker.ps1 #1
+    participant SW2 as spawn-worker.ps1 #2
+    participant WT1 as worktrees/1/
+    participant WT2 as worktrees/2/
+    participant BC1 as Bob CLI #1
+    participant BC2 as Bob CLI #2
+    participant SS as status-server.cjs
+    participant DH as Dashboard
+    
+    User->>FB: Execute
+    FB->>FB: Reset .foreman/
+    FB->>Bob: Estimate tasks
+    Bob-->>FB: estimate.json
+    FB->>FB: Write start_time.txt
+    
+    par Spawn Workers
+        FB->>Job1: Start-Job spawn-worker.ps1 1
+        FB->>Job2: Start-Job spawn-worker.ps1 2
+    end
+    
+    Job1->>SW1: Execute
+    Job2->>SW2: Execute
+    
+    par Worker Execution
+        SW1->>WT1: git worktree add
+        SW1->>SW1: Write tasks/1.json (queued)
+        SW1->>SW1: Update status (running)
+        SW1->>BC1: bob @prompt-1.txt
+        BC1-->>SW1: Output
+        SW1->>SW1: Write logs/1.json
+        SW1->>WT1: git commit
+        SW1->>SW1: Update status (done)
+        
+        SW2->>WT2: git worktree add
+        SW2->>SW2: Write tasks/2.json (queued)
+        SW2->>SW2: Update status (running)
+        SW2->>BC2: bob @prompt-2.txt
+        BC2-->>SW2: Output
+        SW2->>SW2: Write logs/2.json
+        SW2->>WT2: git commit
+        SW2->>SW2: Update status (done)
+    end
+    
+    par Dashboard Polling
+        loop Every 1s
+            DH->>SS: GET /dashboard/status.json
+            SS->>SS: Read .foreman/tasks/*.json
+            SS->>SS: Read logs/*.json
+            SS-->>DH: Aggregated status
+            DH->>DH: Update UI
+        end
+    end
+    
+    FB->>FB: Wait-Job (all)
+    FB->>FB: Write end_time.txt
+    FB-->>User: Complete
+```
+
+## Worker State Machine
+
+```mermaid
+stateDiagram-v2
+    [*] --> queued: spawn-worker.ps1 starts
+    queued --> running: Bob CLI invoked
+    running --> done: Task completed successfully
+    running --> error: Bob CLI failed
+    done --> [*]
+    error --> [*]
+    
+    note right of queued
+        .foreman/tasks/<id>.json
+        status: "queued"
+    end note
+    
+    note right of running
+        Bob CLI executing
+        logs/<id>.json streaming
+    end note
+    
+    note right of done
+        Worktree committed
+        Coins counted
+    end note
+    
+    note right of error
+        Error logged
+        Worktree preserved for debug
+    end note
+```
+
