+## Key Design Decisions
+
+### Git Worktree Isolation
+Jeder Worker lâ”śĂ±uft in eigenem worktree. Verhindert file conflicts bei paralleler Ausfâ”śâ•ťhrung.
+
+**Vorteile:**
+- Zero file locking issues
+- Independent git history per task
+- Easy rollback per worker
+- Parallel commits mâ”śĂ‚glich
+
+### PowerShell Background Jobs
+Native Windows parallelization ohne externe Dependencies.
+
+**Vorteile:**
+- Built-in job management (`Start-Job`, `Wait-Job`)
+- Stdout/stderr capture
+- Exit code handling
+- No npm/node required fâ”śâ•ťr orchestration
+
+### Stateless Status Server
+Server liest nur Files, hâ”śĂ±lt keinen State in Memory.
+
+**Vorteile:**
+- Restart-safe
+- No race conditions
+- Simple debugging (inspect files directly)
+- Multiple consumers mâ”śĂ‚glich (Dashboard + Telegram)
+
+### Vanilla JS Dashboard
+Kein Build-Step, kein Framework overhead.
+
+**Vorteile:**
+- Instant deployment (open HTML file)
+- Zero dependencies
+- Fast polling (1s interval)
+- Easy customization
+
+## Performance Characteristics
+
+**Parallelization:**
+- N workers = N CPU cores utilized
+- Linear speedup bis zu core count
+- Overhead: ~2s fâ”śâ•ťr worktree setup pro worker
+
+**Bottlenecks:**
+- Bob CLI execution time (dominant factor)
+- Git operations (worktree add, commit) - minimal
+- Status server polling - negligible
+
+**Typical Timeline:**
+```
+T+0s:    foreman-build starts
+T+2s:    Estimate complete
+T+3s:    All workers spawned
+T+3-60s: Workers executing (parallel)
+T+60s:   First worker done
+T+120s:  All workers done
+T+121s:  foreman-build complete
+```
+
+## Monitoring & Debugging
+
+**Live Monitoring:**
+- Dashboard: `http://localhost:3001/dashboard/`
+- Status API: `http://localhost:3001/dashboard/status.json`
+
+**Post-Mortem:**
+- Worker logs: `logs/<id>.json`
+- Task status: `.foreman/tasks/<id>.json`
+- Worktree state: `worktrees/<id>/` (preserved on error)
+
+**Common Issues:**
+1. **Worker stuck in "running"**: Check `logs/<id>.json` fâ”śâ•ťr Bob errors
+2. **Worktree conflicts**: Inspect `worktrees/<id>/` git status
+3. **Missing coins**: Verify Bob output format in logs
+4. **Dashboard not updating**: Check status-server.cjs running on :3001
+
+## Future Enhancements
+
+- [ ] Worker retry logic (auto-restart on error)
+- [ ] Dynamic worker scaling (spawn more if queue grows)
+- [ ] Distributed execution (multiple machines)
+- [ ] Real-time log streaming (WebSocket)
+- [ ] Historical run comparison
+- [ ] Cost optimization (coin usage analytics)

